{{Infobox journal | title = African Geographical Review | cover = AGRcover.JPG | image_size = 200px | editor = Isaac Luginaah] | discipline = [[Geography]] | formernames = East African Geographical Review | abbreviation = Afr. Geogr. Rev. | publisher = [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[Africa Specialty Group]] ([[Association of American Geographers]]) | country = | frequency = Biannually | openaccess = | impact = | impact-year = | website = http://www.tandfonline.com/action/aboutThisJournal?journalCode=rafg20 | link1 = http://www.tandfonline.com/toc/rafg20/current | link1-name = Online access | link2 = http://www.tandfonline.com/loi/rafg20 | link2-name = Online archive | JSTOR = | ISSN = 1937-6812 | eISSN = 2163-2642 | OCLC = 51782062 | LCCN = 67038577 }} The '''''African Geographical Review''''' is a biannual [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by [[Taylor & Francis]] on behalf of the [[American Association of Geographers]]' [[Africa Specialty Group]].
The journal was originally established in 1963 at [[Makerere University]] ([[Uganda]]) as the ''East African Geographical Review''. Due to political turmoil in Uganda, the journal had to suspend publication for a number of years. It was renamed as the ''African Geographical Review'' in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web |last=Bakama |first=BakamaNume |title=Brief History of the African Geographical Review |url=http://www.macalester.edu/geography/agr/history.htm |accessdate=2010-01-01}}</ref> Since 2012 it is published by Taylor & Francis.
