{{Expand Spanish|date=December 2012|Albarca de Cantabria (calzado)}}
[[File:Albarcas cantabras.jpg|thumb|250px|'''Cantabrian albarcas''' coloured in black.]] [[File:Albarcas-Cantabria.jpg|250px|thumb|right|Albarcas]]
A '''Cantabrian albarca''' is a rustic wooden shoe in one piece, which has been used particularly by the peasants of [[Cantabria]], [[Green Spain|northern Spain]].<ref name="Las albarcas en El Diario Montañés">{{cite web|url = http://www.eldiariomontanes.es/prensa/20060927/cantabria/albarcas_20060927.html |title = Las albarcas en El Diario Montañés |accessdate =12-05-2008 |language = Spanish}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url = http://www.casasyhotelesrurales.com/html/artesaniacantabria.html |title = Artesanía de Cantabria, en Casas y Hoteles Rurales|accessdate =12-05-2008 |language = Spanish}}</ref><ref name="Gran Enciclopedia de Cantabria">{{cite book|title=Gran Enciclopedia de Cantabria.|year=1985|publisher=Editorial Cantabria|location=[[Santander, Cantabria]]|isbn=84-86420-01-6|author1=Linares Argüelles, Mariano |author2=Pindado Uslé, Jesús |author3=Aedo Pérez, Carlos |chapter=Tomo I}}</ref>
Cantabrian albarcas are similar to other [[clog]]s from [[Europe]], but have significant features and different characteristics in terms of [[woodworking]] process and in their use.<ref name="Gran Enciclopedia de Cantabria"/>
